nge(num_cols)]\n        \n        # Replace -1 in each column with the maximum value of that column\n        for row in range(len(matrix)):\n            for col in range(num_cols):\n                if matrix[row][col] == -1:\n                    matrix[row][col] = max_in_columns[col]\n        \n        return matrix\n```\n\nThis solution first calculates the maximum value for each column and stores these values in a list called `max_in_columns`. It then iterates through the matrix, replacing any `-1` values with the corresponding maximum value from the `max_in_columns` list. Finally, it returns the modified matrix.", "estimated_date": 1707609600000}